    "en": {
      "title": "Elephant removed from crop damage list",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Minister of Agriculture, Wildlife and Forest Resources Conservation, Mr. Mahinda Amaraweera instructed the Secretary of the Ministry of Wildlife and Forest Resources Conservation, Mrs. Chandra Herath to take steps to remove the wild elephant from the list of wild animals that cause crop damage in Sri Lanka.",
        "Among the animals that cause crop damage, the crop damage caused by the wild elephant is the least amount of 20 percent of the total crop damage and about 46 percent of the crop damage is caused by the wild boar, monkey, peacock, wild boar and deer, said the Ministry of Agriculture."
      ],
